Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.72,0:00:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,1.\n- hey, wait a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.53,0:00:33.73,Default,,0,0,0,,here we go.\n[ cell phone ringing ]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.73,0:00:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.73,0:00:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,[ beep ]\n- hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.16,0:00:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,oh, hi, mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.50,0:00:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,ah! no, no. not you.\nnot you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.34,0:00:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,so, it --\nhold on -- hold on.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.07,0:00:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,mom, it's not really\nthe best time for me to talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.11,0:00:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,[ sheep bleat ]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.18,0:00:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,[ tires squeal ]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.85,0:00:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,saturday? sure.\noh, mom, hold on.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.95,0:00:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,mom, hold on.\nmom, i got to go. i got to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.38,0:00:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,okay. i'll talk to you later.\n[ beep ]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.82,0:01:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,[ explosion ]
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.89,0:01:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,ahh!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.36,0:01:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,i lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.63,0:01:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,you were looking a little\ndistracted there.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.39,0:01:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah, but i did pretty good\nin reverse.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.76,0:01:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,uh, all right.\n- [ laughs ]
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.12,0:01:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,--<font color="#ffff00"> captions by vitac</font> --\n<font color="#00ffff">www.vitac.com</font>
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.12,0:01:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,captions paid for by\ndiscovery communications
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.69,0:01:37.79,Default,,0,0,0,,all right, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.79,0:01:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,time to get\nyour racing gloves on.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.26,0:01:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,we have an entire episode\nthat puts the word "dangerous"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.60,0:01:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,into the phrase\n"dangerous driving."
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.80,0:01:45.16,Default,,0,0,0,,like what?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.17,0:01:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,well, we've got a hollywood\ncar chase story to tackle,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.23,0:01:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,that driving at\nhigh speed through traffic,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.67,0:01:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,evading your enemies\nin reverse, is easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.04,0:01:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,but first up,\nwe have a story all about
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.91,0:01:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,the dangers of driving while\ntalking on your cell phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.21,0:02:00.45,Default,,0,0,0,,oh, there's a law against that,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.45,0:02:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,at least as far as\nholding it in your hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.05,0:02:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,exactly,\nbut what is the solution
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.95,0:02:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,for someone who wants to\ntalk on their phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.75,0:02:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,hands-free?\n- hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.86,0:02:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,yup, but there's a myth\nthat there is no improvement
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.19,0:02:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,in safety talking hands-free\nversus holding on to your phone,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.06,0:02:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that they both distract you\njust as much.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.76,0:02:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and i think\nwe should test that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.33,0:02:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,absolutely.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.43,0:02:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator:\ntalking on a handheld phone
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.94,0:02:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,leaves a driver both mentally\nand physically compromised.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.68,0:02:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,going hands-free does eliminate\nhalf the problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.31,0:02:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,but with the other half\nstill there,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.08,0:02:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,some say that it's just\nas dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.98,0:02:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,[ tires squeal,\nglass shatters ]
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.09,0:02:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,hey! hey! hey!\n- hey! hey! hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.96,0:02:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: to find out,\nthe "mythbusters" crew
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.93,0:02:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,have constructed\na classified course
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.46,0:02:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,designed by drive expert\ndave storton.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.07,0:02:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,so the first section here\nis a slalom.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.57,0:02:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,so that's gonna test\ntheir steering ability
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.87,0:02:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,while talking on the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.61,0:03:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: right now\nadam and jamie are being
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.07,0:03:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,deliberately kept in the dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.71,0:03:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,storton:\ncoming out of the slalom,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.34,0:03:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,they'll immediately have to get\non the brakes
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.31,0:03:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,for a low-speed exercise\ncalled the offset lane.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.88,0:03:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: because any\npre-existing knowledge of
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.59,0:03:14.69,Default,,0,0,0,,the route could\ndiscredit their data.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.69,0:03:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,storton:\nonce through that,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.86,0:03:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,we head over to\nwhat's called a t-box.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.23,0:03:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: instead,\nall they know is that
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.76,0:03:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,they must stick to\nthe speed limits
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.36,0:03:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and not clip any cones
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.40,0:03:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,if they're to achieve\na perfect score.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.70,0:03:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,right.\nif you bolt the two together,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.00,0:03:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe some sticky tape\nin the middle,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.74,0:03:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and that should totally --\nokay. hold on, hold on, hold on.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.17,0:03:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,i got a thing to do.\nokay, wait right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.34,0:03:38.81,Default,,0,0,0,,okay, so while we know that\ndriving in a car
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.81,0:03:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,while holding on\nto a cell phone and talking
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.35,0:03:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,is bad --\nsorry, that wasn't for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.22,0:03:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the myth is that driving\nhands-free is just as bad,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.69,0:03:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,that there is no difference
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.05,0:03:48.85,Default,,0,0,0,,between hands-full\nand hands-free.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.86,0:03:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and we are just about to test it\non the course behind me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.46,0:03:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,i can see it from a distance,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.29,0:03:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,but that's as close\nas i'm gonna get
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.76,0:03:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,because my ignorance of this\ncourse is intrinsic to our test.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.60,0:04:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: like adam,\njamie's also going
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.34,0:04:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,that extra mile to make sure\ntheir science is sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.34,0:04:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,adam's gonna run this test\ntwice,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.01,0:04:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,first,\nwith phone held in his hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.74,0:04:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and then, secondly, hands-free.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.05,0:04:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,then, i'm also gonna run\nthe test twice.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.21,0:04:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,but i'm gonna do it\nin the inverse order.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.52,0:04:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the idea here is that\nwe're gonna be able to remove
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.32,0:04:21.85,Default,,0,0,0,,any bias as far as learning,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.86,0:04:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and getting better every time\nwe do the test.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.83,0:04:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.06,0:04:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and while adam warms up\nin the test car...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.89,0:04:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,breaker, breaker.\nwe got a, uh, 5-5-5 on an m.p.b.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.66,0:04:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,i'll take care of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.37,0:04:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: jamie sits down\nin mission control.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.80,0:04:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,all right,\ni've got my questions,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.37,0:04:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,i've got my phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.37,0:04:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll see what we can do to mess\nwith adam's world.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.14,0:04:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,hello, sir.\n- hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.01,0:04:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: with dave riding\nshotgun to mark adam's moves,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.98,0:04:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,it's time to hold the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.22,0:04:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,[ cell phone rings ]
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.32,0:04:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,hello.\n- hello, adam.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.52,0:04:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,i've got my questions ready\nfor you and we're good to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.93,0:05:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,3, 2, 1, here we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.70,0:05:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,okay, so, if you could compete\nwith the olympics,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.40,0:05:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,what event would you\nwant to be in?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.47,0:05:13.91,Default,,0,0,0,,um, if i can compete in\nthe olympics, i would, uh,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.91,0:05:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,hold on a second.\nthere we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.44,0:05:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,hold on, sorry, um,\ni think i would do the luge
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.05,0:05:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,because it requires, i think,\nthe least amount of physical,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.62,0:05:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,uh, acuity.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.45,0:05:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,okay. that's great.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.15,0:05:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,now, uh, i need you to add\nthe first two given numbers
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.56,0:05:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and then add the next number\nto the last number given.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.73,0:05:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.89,0:05:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,8 and 7.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.70,0:05:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,um, 8 and 7 equals 15.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.96,0:05:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,okay, 3.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.47,0:05:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,uh, 10.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.44,0:05:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,excellent. okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.91,0:05:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,for the next test, i'm going to\nread you a list of words
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.21,0:05:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and ask you to repeat them\nin reverse order.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.24,0:05:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,hold on a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.94,0:05:52.41,Default,,0,0,0,,now, this is what you might be\nwondering about the complexity
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.41,0:05:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,of the questions we are asking\neach other while driving.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.18,0:05:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,flamethrower. fire hydrant.\nwater.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.58,0:05:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,why aren't we just reading\n"war and peace" over the phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.92,0:06:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,water. fire hydrant.\nflamethrower.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.16,0:06:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,well, each of our questions\nfalls into a category that
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.79,0:06:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,activates the cognitive portions\nof the brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.26,0:06:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,general knowledge --
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.43,0:06:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,which country has\nthe longest coastline?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.46,0:06:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,uh, the longest coastline\nof any country. china?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.24,0:06:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,all require the driver to use\nthe part of their brain
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.70,0:06:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,to listen at the same time\nas they're trying to use
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.84,0:06:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,another part of\ntheir brain to drive.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.38,0:06:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator:\nadam isn't being judged on
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.98,0:06:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,how well he answers\nthe questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.28,0:06:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,add 1 and 7.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.31,0:06:29.01,Default,,0,0,0,,uh, hold on.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.02,0:06:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,[ laughs ] this is...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.68,0:06:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,10.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.25,0:06:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: it's how well he's\ndriving that's the only metric.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.86,0:06:39.29,Default,,0,0,0,,oh! whoa, whoa.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.29,0:06:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: and the answer to that\nis not very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.63,0:06:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,um, hold on. sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.23,0:06:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: the combination of\none hand on the wheel
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.90,0:06:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and a brain that's multitasking\ninto meltdown means that,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.34,0:06:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,by the end of the test,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.01,0:06:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,adam's flunked\nwith flying colors.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.27,0:06:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,jamie, i'm done.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.58,0:06:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that was awful. [ laughs ]\n[ laughs ]
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.25,0:07:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,well, uh, let's reset\nand see whether
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.21,0:07:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you're still a menace\non the next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.88,0:07:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.55,0:07:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,[ engine sputtering ]\n- okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.49,0:07:12.62,Default,,0,0,0,,um, [bleep].
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.63,0:07:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,well,\ni've completed my first test,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.53,0:07:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and talking on the phone\nwas absolutely awful.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.06,0:07:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and then,\nthe car stopped working.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.30,0:07:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,so we are actually going to\ntransfer all of the cameras
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.47,0:07:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and microphones from inside\nthis car
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.04,0:07:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,to one of\nour production vehicles.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.64,0:07:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and i'm gonna run the test\na second time, hands-free.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.48,0:07:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,i mean, we still consider\nmy first test valid,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.21,0:07:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,just have to do the second one\nin a different car.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.82,0:07:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator:\nso, while the team pushes on,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.05,0:07:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,what else is on the docket?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.59,0:07:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,so driving in reverse.\npaint me a picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.82,0:07:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,well, look,\nour hero, let's say,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.42,0:07:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,is driving down\na one way street.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.83,0:07:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,he thinks he's home free,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.19,0:07:49.99,Default,,0,0,0,,but blocking his path is\na villain in a car.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.00,0:07:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,he's got nowhere to go,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.90,0:07:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,so using the only avenue\nopen to him,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.57,0:07:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the hero throws the car\ninto reverse and backs up,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.64,0:07:59.14,Default,,0,0,0,,bobbing and weaving through\ntraffic at high speed
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.14,0:08:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,to eventually\nevade his chaser.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.31,0:08:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and you wanna know\nif this is possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.84,0:08:05.24,Default,,0,0,0,,i totally do.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.25,0:08:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,we've been trained to drive\nin a lot of different ways
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.65,0:08:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,over the years, but backwards\nisn't one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.32,0:08:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and it involves a lot of\ndifferent skills,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.95,0:08:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,not only driving ability\nand spatial awareness but also,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.35,0:08:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,really, proprioception.\nyeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.22,0:08:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,let's get to driving.\n- okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.57,0:08:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,beautiful day.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.47,0:08:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,wide-open, empty runway.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.47,0:08:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,the conditions are perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.18,0:08:39.58,Default,,0,0,0,,oh, wait.\nwe need a car.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.65,0:08:46.62,Default,,0,0,0,,[ tires squeal ]
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.62,0:08:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,you ordered a car?\nindeed i did, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.19,0:08:51.29,Default,,0,0,0,,perfect timing.\n- [ laughs ]
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.06,0:08:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, the movies are packed\nwith people who can drive well,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.46,0:08:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,but they would lead you to\nbelieve that you could drive
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.23,0:09:02.37,Default,,0,0,0,,forward or reverse,\nhowever you choose.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.37,0:09:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,we are constantly seeing\nour movie heroes racing away
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.04,0:09:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,from the bad guys,\navoiding obstacles,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.91,0:09:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and driving all over the place\nwith the rear end of the car
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.38,0:09:14.45,Default,,0,0,0,,facing the direction\nthat they are actually going.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.45,0:09:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: but before trying out\nany twists or turns...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.88,0:09:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and...that's a quarter mile.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.92,0:09:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator:\nthe guys first want to know if
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.49,0:09:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,cars can even reverse\nhollywood-fast in real life.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.39,0:09:29.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and for that, they're hitting\nthe straightaway.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.33,0:09:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,we've set up a course\nthat's measured.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.90,0:09:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and we're gonna test out\nthese cars,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.93,0:09:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,see how fast they go\nin forward
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.67,0:09:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and compare that to how fast\nthey go in reverse.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.41,0:09:43.37,Default,,0,0,0,,all right, mr. hyneman,\nare you ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.38,0:09:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,i'm good to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.75,0:09:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,all right,\ncommence quarter-mile test
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.58,0:09:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,in 3, 2, 1...go.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.28,0:09:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,[ tires squeal ]
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.52,0:09:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,here it comes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.72,0:09:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,80 per hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.53,0:10:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: it's a good start\nfor their converted cab.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.97,0:10:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,but how will that speed compare\nwhen it's back-to-front?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.60,0:10:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,most cars that\nyou're ever gonna run into
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.34,0:10:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,have only one reverse gear,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.71,0:10:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,which means that the top speed\nof your car in reverse
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.34,0:10:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,is ultimately limited by\nthe reverse gearing
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.18,0:10:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and the speed at which\nthe engine is turning over.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.55,0:10:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,now, will our car\nbe able to go as fast
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.48,0:10:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,as they seem to go in\nthe movies?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.52,0:10:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that is just what\nwe're about to find out.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.82,0:10:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,okay, commence backwards\nquarter mile in 3, 2, 1...go.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.69,0:10:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: jamie's off.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.79,0:10:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,but from the get-go,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.16,0:10:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,it's clear that he's less\n"fast and furious"...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.77,0:10:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,...and more\n"driving miss daisy."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.11,0:10:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,but that's because he's using\nthis run to get his eye in.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.04,0:10:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,31 miles per hour.\ni think he can do better.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.55,0:10:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,i think he's got more.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.11,0:10:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator:\nyup, it's test two,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.38,0:10:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,where the rubber will meet\nthe road.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.05,0:11:01.99,Default,,0,0,0,,okay, adam, i'm in place\nand ready to go in reverse.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.99,0:11:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator:\nas jamie, this time,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.22,0:11:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,plans to put the pedal\nto the metal.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.53,0:11:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,all right, mr. hyneman,\nin 3, 2, 1...go.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.27,0:11:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,49, 50, 52, 53.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.18,0:11:28.11,Default,,0,0,0,,54 miles per hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.11,0:11:30.25,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator:\nnow, that's more like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.25,0:11:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,reaching freeway speeds\nis more than a match
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.79,0:11:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,for a hollywood hero,\nbut it's not all good news.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.09,0:11:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,the trick with driving\nat high speed in reverse
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.66,0:11:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,was to not do very much,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.56,0:11:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,just kind of hold still\nand try and keep the car
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.90,0:11:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,in a straight line.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.46,0:11:47.70,Default,,0,0,0,,but unfortunately, we're not\ngoing to have that option now
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.70,0:11:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,because, now we've got to drive\nthrough a slalom in reverse.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.70,0:11:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's all about steering.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.91,0:11:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,that's gonna be really hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.98,0:11:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: still to come...\nbye, cop.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.61,0:12:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: backup bologna\ngets a movie makeover.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.78,0:12:02.58,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.58,0:12:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: and...\n- hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.25,0:12:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,...hands-free goes high-tech.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.49,0:12:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,ahh!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.52,0:12:10.45,Default,,0,0,0,,[ laughs ]
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.36,0:12:18.66,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: is driving at speed\nin reverse
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.66,0:12:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,as easy as the movies make out?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.87,0:12:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,[ tires squeal ]
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.30,0:12:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,well, not if adam's\nstraight line test...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.50,0:12:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,jamie: coming up fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.14,0:12:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator:\n...is anything to go by.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.57,0:12:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,adam: ahh!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.18,0:12:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,[ tires squeal ]
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.84,0:12:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.05,0:12:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,there are a couple reasons that\ncars are difficult to drive
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.45,0:12:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,at high speed in reverse.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.12,0:12:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,[ laughs ] hey. yeah, you\nstarted to lose it at about 50.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.39,0:12:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah, man.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.92,0:12:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,jamie: and the first is that
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.09,0:12:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the steering is not\nself-centering.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.36,0:12:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,if you let go of the wheel\nof a car going forward
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.86,0:12:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,for just a second,\nit'll tend to self-correct
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.76,0:12:52.93,Default,,0,0,0,,because of the offset\nof the wheels.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.93,0:12:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,if you're going in reverse,\nit does the opposite.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.40,0:12:56.97,Default,,0,0,0,,if you let go of that wheel,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.97,0:12:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,you're gonna go hard\nto the side,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.97,0:13:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're gonna do a 180,\nand that's dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.37,0:13:05.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and correct a little too much,\nyou're gonna lose it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.24,0:13:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the other thing is that\nit's all about perspective.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.35,0:13:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,when you're going forwards,\nwith your head in align
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.11,0:13:11.41,Default,,0,0,0,,with the steering wheel,\ndriving's really intuitive.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.42,0:13:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,but in reverse, you're either\nlooking into the mirror
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.19,0:13:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,or over your shoulder,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.65,0:13:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,meaning your brain's having to\nmake complex decisions
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.52,0:13:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,from a viewpoint\nthat it's just not used to.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.03,0:13:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,[ tires squeal ]
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.59,0:13:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and so, when things go wrong,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.33,0:13:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,you're gonna flip the car\nor something bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.87,0:13:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: given their struggles\non the straightaway,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.57,0:13:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,today's test looks terrifying.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.07,0:13:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,this is what we call the "diving\nin at the deep end" test.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.81,0:13:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,we've got a course that's full\nof the kind of challenges
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.14,0:13:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,a hollywood hero has to face,\nand we're going to see if we can
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.15,0:13:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,reverse through it\nat high speeds without crashing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.72,0:13:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,[ laughs ]\nthis is why we have insurance.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.92,0:13:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: it's a course that\na movie maestro
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.22,0:13:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,would finish in a flash.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.92,0:13:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,but how will\nthe mythbusters manage?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.33,0:14:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.60,0:14:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,first run in 3, 2, 1...go.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.31,0:14:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: adam's off.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.01,0:14:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and from the outset,\nhe's ignoring the mirrors...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.08,0:14:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,whoa.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.45,0:14:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,oh, there goes a cone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.98,0:14:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: and going with\nthe over-the-shoulder technique.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.62,0:14:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,ah, [bleep]!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.69,0:14:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: but it's hardly\npaying dividends.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.36,0:14:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,because not only poor steering\ncripple his cone count...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.56,0:14:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,ah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.37,0:14:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: but his slow speed\nmeans his time is terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.30,0:14:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,[ laughs ]
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.57,0:14:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,how did i do?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.57,0:14:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,1 minute 7 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.88,0:14:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,1 minute, 7 seconds?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.81,0:14:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,i'll tell you what that does.\nit wreaks havoc on my neck.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.55,0:14:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,well, i-i had a couple of\nscrewups on that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.22,0:15:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,it's very hard to gauge\nhow hard you need to
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.06,0:15:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,hit a turn in reverse
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.90,0:15:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,because all of your metrics\nfor reaction,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.16,0:15:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,in terms of how the car moves,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.90,0:15:09.37,Default,,0,0,0,,are way off-kilter.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.37,0:15:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a far more sensitive\ndevice in reverse.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.84,0:15:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: indeed,\nbut can jamie master the method
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.48,0:15:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and reverse\nthis myth's fortunes?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.11,0:15:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,[ engine starts ]\nall right, cowboy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.61,0:15:23.81,Default,,0,0,0,,here we go\nin 3, 2, 1...go.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.82,0:15:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,[ tires squeal ]
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.09,0:15:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,[ laughs ]\ni love that this is our job.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.92,0:15:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: unlike adam,\njamie's using the mirrors
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.52,0:15:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and the over-the-shoulder\nsystem.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.76,0:15:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's not\na winning combination...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.16,0:15:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,[ tires squeal ]\n[ laughing ]
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.13,0:15:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,[ shifts gears ]
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.37,0:15:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator:\nbecause his crash course
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.97,0:15:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,is even worse than adam's.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.24,0:15:49.97,Default,,0,0,0,,but eventually,\nhe crawls to the finish line
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.98,0:15:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,in a sluggish 72 seconds...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.74,0:15:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,[ tires screech ]\n[ laughs ]
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.08,0:15:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,[ groans ]
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.05,0:16:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: ...which is not\ngood news for the myth.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.42,0:16:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,okay, you win.\n- [ laughs ]
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.85,0:16:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator:\nbut all is not lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.16,0:16:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,look, there is no doubt that\nthis test was hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.29,0:16:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.76,0:16:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the course was difficult,\nand we are at the novice end
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.76,0:16:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,of the reverse driving spectrum.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.47,0:16:15.70,Default,,0,0,0,,but with some expert training,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.70,0:16:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,will we be able to bring this\nmyth back from the brink?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.40,0:16:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,that's what's next.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.14,0:16:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator:\nactually, not quite.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.77,0:16:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,because next, the guys are\njumping ship back to alameda
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.71,0:16:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,to find out if hands-free is\nas distracting
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.52,0:16:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,as holding the phone.\n[ cell phone rings ]
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.12,0:16:34.45,Default,,0,0,0,,uh, hello, jamie.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.45,0:16:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: adam started\nwith a hands-full control...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.76,0:16:39.29,Default,,0,0,0,,oh, whoa. whoa.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.29,0:16:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator:\nthat went so badly...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.26,0:16:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.33,0:16:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator:\nhis car refused to continue.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.56,0:16:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,okay.\n- [ engine sputters ]
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.93,0:16:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator:\nso it's out with the old.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.80,0:16:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,all right, dave.\nlet's do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.00,0:16:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator:\nand in with the new.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.37,0:16:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,but will going hands-free\nreally be just as bad?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.94,0:16:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,[ line ringing ]\nhere we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.71,0:16:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,[ beep ]\n- why, hello, this is adam.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.48,0:17:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,well, hello there, adam.\nshould i start driving?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.05,0:17:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,yes. go ahead.\n- okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.08,0:17:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: like last time,\nadam must complete the course
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.22,0:17:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,while answering questions\nboth easy...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.65,0:17:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,okay, on which continent is\nthe sahara desert?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.09,0:17:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the sahara desert is on\nthe african continent.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.86,0:17:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: and hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.76,0:17:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,if buster walks halfway\naround a circle
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.80,0:17:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and then turns around\nand walks halfway back,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.83,0:17:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,is he now back\nwhere he started?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.67,0:17:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,yes, he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.20,0:17:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,no, he's halfway back.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.31,0:17:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,[ laughs ]\n- ah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.91,0:17:30.27,Default,,0,0,0,,okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.28,0:17:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: but despite\nthe obvious burden on his brain,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.55,0:17:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,his driving has got better.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.45,0:17:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and although a clipped cone\nsees him marked down...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.89,0:17:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,[ laughing ]\n- [ laughs ]
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.95,0:17:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,sorry.\ni just hit something.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.29,0:17:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator:\nhis final score has improved,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.96,0:17:49.33,Default,,0,0,0,,but was it due to the phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.33,0:17:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,adam: well, i've completed\nmy hands-free run
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.66,0:17:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,of our driving course,\nand i did it a lot better.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.20,0:17:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,but here's the thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.64,0:18:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,i found taking the questions\nfrom jamie just as distracting
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.17,0:18:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,as i did the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.57,0:18:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,i feel like my better\nperformance on the second test
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.98,0:18:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,could be chalked up to just\nunderstanding the course
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.48,0:18:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,a little bit better.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.78,0:18:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,but that's why jamie's\ngonna start hands-free
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.92,0:18:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and then go to hands-full.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.39,0:18:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,if that is in effect,\nwe should cancel it out
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.39,0:18:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,by changing the order\nthat we do the test in.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.72,0:18:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the theory, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.30,0:18:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,want to see\nwhat you can do with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.53,0:18:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,i'm gonna suck.\ni can tell you already.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.60,0:18:31.77,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: not only will jamie\nincrease their sample size,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.77,0:18:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,but by going hands-free first...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.07,0:18:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,jamie and i almost never\nactually speak on the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.68,0:18:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,so this actually has a bit of\nnovelty to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.54,0:18:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator:\nthe guys are trying to eliminate
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.65,0:18:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,any course-learning bias.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.05,0:18:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,[ line ringing ]\nthis is jamie.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.92,0:18:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,ah, good afternoon, jamie.\nit's adam.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.82,0:18:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,go ahead and start driving,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.36,0:18:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and i'm going to start\nasking you some questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.16,0:18:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: adam starts\nwith a simple icebreaker.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.59,0:18:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,all right, hey, jamie,\nif you could wake up tomorrow
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.96,0:19:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and gain any single\nquality or ability,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.70,0:19:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,what would it be and why?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.93,0:19:06.37,Default,,0,0,0,,um, i could fly.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.37,0:19:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,why?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.71,0:19:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: but even that proves\ntoo much for jamie.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.61,0:19:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,well, uh,\nbecause then i could go, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.84,0:19:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,what was the question again?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.51,0:19:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,why would you like to fly?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.11,0:19:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,uh, well, because,\nthat would, uh,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.49,0:19:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,it would save a lot of\ngasoline actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.19,0:19:25.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and, uh, you know,\ni could, uh,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.89,0:19:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,oh, look at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.96,0:19:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,i bumped over\na whole bunch of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.36,0:19:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,[ laughs ]
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.89,0:19:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: with no improvement\nover the rest of the course...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.33,0:19:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,i'd like you to add\nthe numbers 4 and 7.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.67,0:19:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,let's see.\nuh, 4 and 7, uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.80,0:19:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.14,0:19:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,ticktock, grandpa.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.54,0:19:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,10 -- or, no, 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.54,0:19:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: jamie scores\nthe worst result of the day --
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.38,0:19:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,a disappointing 66.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.75,0:19:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,that was awesome.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.49,0:19:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,he starts every answer\nwith, "let's see." [ laughs ]
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.66,0:19:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,i'm sure i was doing\nthe same things,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.89,0:20:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's just very enjoyable to\nlisten to someone so distracted.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.66,0:20:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator:\na quick reset later,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.36,0:20:07.73,Default,,0,0,0,,[ cell phone rings ]
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.73,0:20:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and they're set for\nthe fourth and final run...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.30,0:20:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.97,0:20:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,all right.\nstart your driving.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.04,0:20:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator:\njamie, hands-full.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.54,0:20:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,i'm going to read you\na list of words
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.77,0:20:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and ask you to repeat them\nin a reverse order.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.01,0:20:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,crash, burn, demolish.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.38,0:20:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,uh, demolish, uh, burn, crash.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.92,0:20:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,e.m.t., ambulance, doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.52,0:20:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,there's quite a narrative\nimplied by these.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.85,0:20:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,doctor, ambulance, e.m.t.\n- yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.16,0:20:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: despite having only\none hand on the wheel
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.03,0:20:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and swapping the phone\nmid-drive, jamie scores 72,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.46,0:20:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,a fail by some distance,\nbut an improvement nonetheless.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.60,0:20:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,so, what does this mean\nfor the myth?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.84,0:20:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,okay, now,\nfor this myth to be true,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.77,0:20:51.74,Default,,0,0,0,,jamie's hands-free score had to\nmatch his hands-full score.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.74,0:20:52.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and so did mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.91,0:20:55.45,Default,,0,0,0,,but that didn't quite happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.45,0:20:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,graphics, help me out.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.65,0:20:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,you can see that i drove better\nhands-free,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.32,0:21:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,while jamie drove\nbetter hands-full.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.49,0:21:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,but that data also shows\nthat we both improved on
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.22,0:21:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,our second runs because we had\nexperience of the course.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.86,0:21:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,now, if we remove that bias by\naveraging jamie's and my data,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.00,0:21:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,what do we get?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.83,0:21:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,beautiful,\nnear-identical scores
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.63,0:21:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,for each of the two techniques.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.90,0:21:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,but we are not done yet,\nfor two particular reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.21,0:21:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,one, our course\nisn't very real-world.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.94,0:21:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,for starters,\nthere's no traffic.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.15,0:21:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,second,\nand perhaps more importantly,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.05,0:21:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,is jamie's\nand my driving abilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.92,0:21:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,we have both received\ntons of training over the years
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.89,0:21:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,in lots of different\ndriving techniques.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.55,0:21:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.76,0:21:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,whoo, yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.32,0:21:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,we are quite far\nfrom your average joes,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.59,0:21:42.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is what we need next.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.40,0:21:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,aah!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.70,0:21:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,3, 2, 1...go.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.81,0:21:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,[ tires squeal ]
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.34,0:21:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,adam: now, jamie and i have\nalready gone pretty far,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.04,0:22:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,teaching ourselves the rudiments\nof driving in reverse.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.94,0:22:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,[ tires squeal ]
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.58,0:22:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,[ laughs ]
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.78,0:22:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,but if we're gonna get\nreally good at this,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.72,0:22:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,we're gonna need to\nget trained by an expert.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.69,0:22:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,luckily, we have an expert\nin reverse tactical driving
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.09,0:22:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.16,0:22:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,hello, sir. hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.76,0:22:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,jamie:\nbrian frazer is a trainer
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.03,0:22:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,at the emergency vehicle\noperations course
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.03,0:22:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,here in california.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.57,0:22:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,now, we've used him repeatedly\nover past years,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.40,0:22:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,whenever we've had to learn\nhow to deal with a particularly
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.90,0:22:30.81,Default,,0,0,0,,difficult driving situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.81,0:22:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and driving at speed\nin reverse certainly qualifies.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.25,0:22:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,all right, brian.\nwhere do we start?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.25,0:22:40.62,Default,,0,0,0,,we're going to put barrel here,\ntwo barrels here,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.62,0:22:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,one on each side of the car.\nall right.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.82,0:22:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: brian's first job is\nto ignore the current course...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.66,0:22:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,right there is good.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.09,0:22:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,good. good ending point.\naw.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.89,0:22:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,this is why we can't have\nnice things.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.16,0:22:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: and set up something\nway more straightforward...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.33,0:22:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,all right, that's the course.\nnow what do we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.64,0:23:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,drive it.\n- okay. let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.80,0:23:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: because the technique\nhe's going to teach
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.44,0:23:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,is surprisingly simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.44,0:23:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,so i'm gonna change\nmy seating position now
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.98,0:23:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,a little bit.\n- okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.48,0:23:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,i'm going to prop myself up,\nloosen my seat belt.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.75,0:23:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,turn yourself as far as\nyou can around.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.68,0:23:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,get your body almost in\nthe center of the -- of the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.59,0:23:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.02,0:23:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,i'm gonna steer the car now\nwith one hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.89,0:23:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,but this hand will never leave\nthe steering wheel.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.12,0:23:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,not -- you're not gonna let\nthe steering wheel
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.23,0:23:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,shift in your hand to lock.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.36,0:23:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,you're -- you're palming\nthe wheel the entire time.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.20,0:23:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,i see. okay, cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.53,0:23:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator:\nand believe it or not,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.70,0:23:32.87,Default,,0,0,0,,that's apparently\nall there is to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.87,0:23:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,3, 2, 1...go.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.97,0:23:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: by shifting his body\nto the center of the car...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.81,0:23:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,[ laughs ] oh, wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.98,0:23:50.95,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: and keeping one hand\non the wheel at all times...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.95,0:23:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,wow, i can't believe how fast\nyou're able to do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.96,0:23:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator:\nbrian speeds through the course
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.79,0:23:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,at an impressive\n41 miles per hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.93,0:24:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that is amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.80,0:24:05.37,Default,,0,0,0,,adam: so brian just showed me\nthat something i thought was
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.37,0:24:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,impossible is in fact,\ntotally possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.31,0:24:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,so i'm about to give that\na shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.54,0:24:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,this is gonna be cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.08,0:24:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: like brian,\nadam slides to the center
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.85,0:24:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,to give a viewpoint\nthat's easier to process.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.12,0:24:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,oh, look at that.\n- yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.25,0:24:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,okay, so. all right.\n3, 2, 1...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.96,0:24:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: and like brian,\nhe then nails the course.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.66,0:24:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,oh, that's so cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.66,0:24:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: to check it wasn't\njust beginner's luck,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.90,0:24:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,he tries again\nand goes even faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.50,0:24:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,awesome.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.74,0:24:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,jamie: i got to say,\nthis is amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.17,0:24:44.61,Default,,0,0,0,,when we got here this morning,\ni thought adam was gonna be
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.61,0:24:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,training for four, five,\nmaybe six hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.14,0:24:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's not been\nlike that at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.68,0:24:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,instead,\nin just 20 minutes,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.32,0:24:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,he's gone from being pretty\naverage to being pretty great.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.82,0:24:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and it seems to be all down to\nthe central head position,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.36,0:25:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,which seems to be letting\nadam's brain process
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.19,0:25:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the direction to turn\nmuch more accurately.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.16,0:25:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,so, we're gonna put him back on\nour original course to see
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.70,0:25:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,how he does now.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.40,0:25:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,should be interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.01,0:25:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: it's the course\nthe guys couldn't crack.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.67,0:25:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,so, you ready to put what you\nlearned into practice?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.84,0:25:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,i am. in fact, i can't wait to\ntry this course now.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.02,0:25:30.29,Default,,0,0,0,,3, 2, 1...go.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.29,0:25:32.49,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: but will\nhis 20 minutes of training
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.49,0:25:34.89,Default,,0,0,0,,let adam turn it around?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.89,0:25:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,he's off to a good start.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.73,0:25:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,turns are a lot\nsmoother this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.93,0:25:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,he's looking really good.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.06,0:25:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.67,0:25:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,well, yeah.\nhe's moving pretty quick.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.53,0:25:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,coming in good.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.70,0:25:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.84,0:25:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,tell me, tell me, tell me,\ntell me, tell me, tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.24,0:25:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,tell me, tell me how i did.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.54,0:25:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,57.25.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.54,0:25:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,boom! that was cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.81,0:26:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: it's close to\nan astounding result.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.98,0:26:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,with just two minor\nmodifications...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.29,0:26:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,adam: yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.49,0:26:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: adam's bettered\nhis best by over 15%.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.02,0:26:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,all right, guess it's time to\nbring on the next event.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.46,0:26:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,[ tires squeal ]
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.53,0:26:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator:\nand what that means is,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.43,0:26:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,it's time for some\nreal-life movie mayhem.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.90,0:26:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,but first...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.30,0:26:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,hold the phone...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.91,0:26:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,because,\nin driving distracted,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.68,0:26:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,neither adam nor jamie\ncould drive safely
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.65,0:26:31.95,Default,,0,0,0,,while talking hands-free.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.06,0:26:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,but now, in a location way\nmore sophisticated...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.49,0:26:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,[ laughs ] it's locked.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.26,0:26:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator:\nit's time to up the ante.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.00,0:26:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,jamie and i have realized\nwe need much more controlled,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.03,0:26:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,scientific\nand realistic conditions,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.57,0:26:56.87,Default,,0,0,0,,which is why we've come here to\nenlist the help of the experts
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.87,0:27:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,at the stanford university\nautomotive innovation facility.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.54,0:27:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,when we asked for their help\nin getting more realistic,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.28,0:27:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,they showed us a virtual world.\ncome here.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.75,0:27:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,this is their state-of-the-art\ndriving simulator.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.55,0:27:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,it is awesome.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.85,0:27:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,from the front seat of this car,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.52,0:27:15.29,Default,,0,0,0,,you are completely immersed\nin a world controlled
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.29,0:27:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and designed by a computer,\ninto which we can add
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.06,0:27:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,all sorts of traffic,\npedestrians, obstacles,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.20,0:27:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and surprises for all of our\ntest subjects, that's right,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.20,0:27:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,many, many test subjects,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.77,0:27:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,while we get to the bottom of\nthis myth.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.17,0:27:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: it's a multi-million\ndollar machine...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.84,0:27:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,all right, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.21,0:27:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,going for a drive\nin the simulator.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.25,0:27:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: which jamie\ncan't resist turning up to 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.52,0:27:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,[ strained voice ]\nokay, here we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.72,0:27:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,[ laughs ]\n[ horn honks ]
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.35,0:27:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,i'm gonna go the other way.\nwhoa. this is crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.89,0:27:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,ah... [ imitates crash sound ]
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.56,0:27:54.33,Default,,0,0,0,,[ laughs ]
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.33,0:27:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,crazy driving aside,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.87,0:27:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,this driving simulator is\nactually very good.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.50,0:28:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah, get out of my way.\n[ laughs ]
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.94,0:28:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,[ horn honking ]
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.37,0:28:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the way the screen wraps around,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.34,0:28:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the visuals are\nconvincing enough
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.24,0:28:10.04,Default,,0,0,0,,that you have to remind yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.05,0:28:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,that this isn't\na real driving scenario.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.72,0:28:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,he's doing, like, 95.\ninteresting.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.72,0:28:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,i'll see how he likes this.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.19,0:28:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,[ horn blares ]
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.42,0:28:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,in fact, it's so good that
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.83,0:28:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,i was starting\nto get a little carsick.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.96,0:28:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,so i think, as far as\ntesting distracted driving,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.60,0:28:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,it's as good a simulation\nas we're going to get.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.17,0:28:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator:\nas well as the freeway...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.64,0:28:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,[ laughing ]
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.97,0:28:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: there's also\na detailed cityscape...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.68,0:28:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,[ laughs ] oh, i guess\ni better put it in reverse.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.25,0:28:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: ...so that all\ndriving environments are tested.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.32,0:28:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,[ jamie laughs ]
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.52,0:28:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator:\nthe 30 volunteer drivers
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.42,0:28:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,will be judged on whether\nthey pay attention
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.56,0:28:57.39,Default,,0,0,0,,to the gps instructions...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.39,0:28:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>automated male voice:</i>\n<i>at the next intersection,</i>
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.70,0:28:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>turn left.</i>
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.93,0:29:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: ...and whether or not\nthey crash.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.77,0:29:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,[ tires squeal ]\nah!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.40,0:29:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator:\nbut that's not the only data,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.14,0:29:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,because drivers will also wear\nthe latest
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.47,0:29:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,in eye-tracking technology.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.14,0:29:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,this eye-tracking system records\nprecisely where and how long
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.81,0:29:16.54,Default,,0,0,0,,i'm looking at something.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.55,0:29:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,now, that's gonna give us\nhard data as to the level of
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.15,0:29:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,distraction that i'm\nexperiencing while i'm driving.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.99,0:29:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: with eagle-eyed jamie\nall wired up,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.59,0:29:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,he's going to be the first\ndata of the day...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.72,0:29:28.49,Default,,0,0,0,,all right.\ncalling him now.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.49,0:29:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,[ cell phone ringing ]
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.59,0:29:31.49,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator:\nstarting after the break.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.49,0:29:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.14,0:29:46.11,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: using a phone\non the road is bad news,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.11,0:29:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,but is going hands-free\njust as foolish?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.98,0:29:54.85,Default,,0,0,0,,to find out,\nthe mythbusters have a simulator
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.85,0:29:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,that's second to none...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.15,0:29:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,[ laughs ] i love this thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.89,0:30:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,all right.\ncalling him now.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.66,0:30:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: and a hyneman\nthat's got his hands full.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.89,0:30:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,hello?\n- good morning, mr. hyneman.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.13,0:30:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,are you ready to start\nthis test?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.16,0:30:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,i'm ready.\n- okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.77,0:30:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,kick the car into drive,\nstart driving,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.83,0:30:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and i'll start asking\nyou some questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.17,0:30:16.97,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: the questions are\nsimilar to those posed before.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.97,0:30:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,did you play a musical\ninstrument as a child, jamie?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.24,0:30:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah, i had a-a tuba\nin the bathroom
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.21,0:30:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,right next to the toilet\nthat i would play when i was,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.98,0:30:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, doing number two\nor something.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.88,0:30:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,[ laughs ]
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.09,0:30:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: but what's interesting\nis that, on the freeway...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.66,0:30:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,speed, underwater, camera.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.66,0:30:36.49,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator:\njamie's driving...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.49,0:30:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,hold on. you know, somebody just\npulled in front of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.09,0:30:40.49,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator:\nand answers...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.50,0:30:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,camera, underwater, speed.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.90,0:30:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator:\nare surprisingly solid.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.83,0:30:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,in fact, it's only\nwhen he hits the streets...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.40,0:30:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,12 and 7.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.94,0:30:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator:\nthat he starts to waver.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.51,0:30:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,okay, uh, let's see.\nuh, 19.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.01,0:30:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator:\nwith so many distractions,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.05,0:31:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,it's no surprise when jamie\ntakes a turn for the worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.48,0:31:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>automated male voice:</i>\n<i>at the next intersection,</i>
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.22,0:31:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>turn left.</i>
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.65,0:31:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,[ signal clicking ]
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.42,0:31:09.99,Default,,0,0,0,,jamie,\nyou have taken a wrong turn,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.99,0:31:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and that means that\nthe test is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.50,0:31:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,you have failed.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.73,0:31:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.83,0:31:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator:\nwith no rest for the wicked,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.60,0:31:19.70,Default,,0,0,0,,jamie immediately moves on to\nthe hands-free test.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.70,0:31:21.10,Default,,0,0,0,,hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.10,0:31:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the longest running race\nin the olympic games called?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.84,0:31:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,the longest running race in, uh,\nin the olympic game is
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.31,0:31:32.35,Default,,0,0,0,,called a maradon.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.35,0:31:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,a maradon?\n- maradon.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.25,0:31:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,you mean marathon?\n- yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.95,0:31:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.29,0:31:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: once again,\njamie's focused on the freeway
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.72,0:31:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,but struggles in the city\nas his brain tries to process
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.93,0:31:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,the traffic\nand the conversation.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.50,0:31:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the earth is located\nin what galaxy?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.87,0:31:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,uh, the, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.00,0:31:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, i don't know\nthe answer to that question.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.97,0:31:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator:\nlike last time...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.38,0:32:00.37,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>automated male voice:</i>\n<i>at the next intersection,</i>
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.38,0:32:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,<i>turn left.</i>
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.51,0:32:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator:\njamie doesn't crash,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.65,0:32:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,but he does ignore the gps...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.95,0:32:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,oh, i'm sorry.\ni screwed this up.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.42,0:32:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator:\n...meaning he's failed again.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.35,0:32:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,well, the long and the short\nof it is that jamie has done
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.02,0:32:14.09,Default,,0,0,0,,this test twice\nin our virtual environment,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.09,0:32:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,once holding the phone,\nonce hands-free,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.96,0:32:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and he has failed both times.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.23,0:32:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,it's looking pretty good\nfor this myth,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.66,0:32:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,but we are not leaving it here.\nno, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.83,0:32:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,we're going to funnel\na whole bunch of volunteers
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.53,0:32:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,through this testing procedure\nto get some real numbers
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.04,0:32:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,to back up\nour potential conclusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.74,0:32:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: first of\nthe 30 volunteers is tiffany,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.58,0:32:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,who will be driving\nhands-full.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.98,0:32:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the first thing i want to know\nis what musical instrument
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.35,0:32:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,you played as a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.22,0:32:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,none.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.72,0:32:50.99,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: on the freeway,\nher driving is solid...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.99,0:32:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,,logic questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.23,0:32:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator:\nand her answers are perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.86,0:32:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,name four days that start\nwith the letter "t."
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.70,0:32:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,today, tomorrow, tuesday,\nand thursday.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.30,0:33:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,excellent.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.54,0:33:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: but moments\nafter hitting the city...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.31,0:33:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,how much dirt is --
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.81,0:33:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,oh, we just ran down\na cyclist.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.25,0:33:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,this test is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.42,0:33:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,[ line ringing ]
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.35,0:33:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator:\nnext up is michael.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.39,0:33:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.82,0:33:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: and, hands-free,\nhe's fine on the freeway...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.42,0:33:23.66,Default,,0,0,0,,what is something you have at\nhome that you should throw away,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.66,0:33:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,but you can't?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.89,0:33:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,ah, my old computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.70,0:33:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,i still have one that\ngot built in, like, '95.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.57,0:33:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator:\nbut deadly downtown.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.60,0:33:35.14,Default,,0,0,0,,um, which country --\n[ tires squeal ]
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.14,0:33:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,oh! ahh.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.14,0:33:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,i-i believe that might be\nthe end of our test there,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.21,0:33:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,michael.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.38,0:33:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,where did that come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.68,0:33:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,[ laughs ]
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.65,0:33:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,thank you very much, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.28,0:33:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,[ bleep ]
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.39,0:33:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator:\nwhen the next four volunteers
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.59,0:33:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,also crash and burn...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.59,0:33:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.42,0:33:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator:\nit's looking good for the myth.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.33,0:34:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,stop the car and, please,\nlicense and registration, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.73,0:34:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator:\nand although driver seven
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.47,0:34:05.77,Default,,0,0,0,,does make it through\nthe course intact...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.77,0:34:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,all right,\nuh, congratulations.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.14,0:34:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,you have successfully\ncompleted the test.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.10,0:34:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator:\nnearly all other drivers,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.14,0:34:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,whatever their phone fashion,\neither get lost...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.31,0:34:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,uh, ron, i'm sorry to inform you\nthat you have now missed a turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.15,0:34:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and thus, the test is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.68,0:34:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: ...or worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.75,0:34:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,oh, we had a crash,\ndidn't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.42,0:34:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: undeterred,\nthe guys plow on
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.92,0:34:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,through two full days of\ntesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.13,0:34:34.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and when volunteer 30\ntakes dramatic evasive action...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.93,0:34:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,[ laughs ] i suck at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.33,0:34:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: the guys have all\nthe data they could hope for.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.57,0:34:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,all right,\nwe have run a lot of volunteers
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.10,0:34:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,through this experiment,\nand we've got a lot of data
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.21,0:34:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to take a look at.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.44,0:34:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,so it's time to leave\nthis virtual world,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.28,0:34:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,drive through the real world,\nback to our shop,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.91,0:34:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and crunch the numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.22,0:34:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,no way.\nthey said that?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.75,0:35:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,that is hilarious.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.12,0:35:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,hold on just a second.\nwhat?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.39,0:35:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,we were waiting for the results\non distracted driving.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.39,0:35:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,oh, okay.\nuh, i got to call you back.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.90,0:35:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,[ beep ]\n- yes, we have results.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.23,0:35:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,we tested 30 drivers out\nin stanford, 15 hands-full,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.47,0:35:12.87,Default,,0,0,0,,15 hands-free.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.87,0:35:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,here is the result.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.47,0:35:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,uh, hands-full -- one passed,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.21,0:35:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,five failed by driving the wrong\nway, nine failed by crashing.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.58,0:35:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,hands-free -- one passed,\nsix failed by getting lost,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.15,0:35:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and eight failed by crashing.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.78,0:35:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,what's that mean\nstatistically?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.32,0:35:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,statistically,\nit means no difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.95,0:35:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and what about eye tracking?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.45,0:35:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the eye tracker\nwas very interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.22,0:35:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,across all 30 drivers,\nthe amount of time they spent
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.49,0:35:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,looking at something\nother than the road
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.39,0:35:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,was identical between\nhands-free and hands-full.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.36,0:35:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,well, there you have it.\n[ cell phone beeps ]
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.00,0:35:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,don't use your cell phone\nwhile you're driving.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.47,0:35:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah, i'm done. okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.00,0:35:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,so, where do you want to\nmeet for lunch? absolutely.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.78,0:35:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: coming right up,\nthe guys rev in reverse...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.75,0:36:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.35,0:36:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator:\nfor a confounding conclusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.19,0:36:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,[ tires squeal ]\nah!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.39,0:36:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: in driving in reverse,\nthere's a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.00,0:36:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,we -- we can't catch\na break today.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.97,0:36:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,we just rolled up the windows
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.13,0:36:21.10,Default,,0,0,0,,'cause the wind's\nso diabolical,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.10,0:36:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and we locked the keys inside.\n[ laughs ]
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.01,0:36:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: luckily, for once,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.27,0:36:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a cop around\nwhen you need him.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.98,0:36:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,hey!\n- bingo.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.58,0:36:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,[ laughs ]
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.32,0:36:38.62,Default,,0,0,0,,mythbusters,\nrepossessing cars since 1979.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.93,0:36:48.43,Default,,0,0,0,,[ tires squeal ]
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.43,0:36:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,it's all about reverse driving\nin this episode,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.73,0:36:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and how easy it is versus how\neasy hollywood makes it seem.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.23,0:36:56.13,Default,,0,0,0,,whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.14,0:36:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,jamie and i have tried out\nsome courses ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.04,0:37:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,[ tires squeal ]
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.17,0:37:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,[ laughs ]
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.98,0:37:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,we've been trained by a cop\nwho is an expert
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.24,0:37:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,in driving in reverse.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.45,0:37:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,here we go. 3, 2...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.55,0:37:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the reverse.\n- oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.68,0:37:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,there we go.\n- thank you. [ laughs ]
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.95,0:37:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,so now, it's time for me\nto take all of the skills
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.92,0:37:15.99,Default,,0,0,0,,i've thus far learned\nand put them to a real test.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.99,0:37:17.99,Default,,0,0,0,,i'm here at\nan abandoned neighborhood
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.99,0:37:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,in marina, california, where my\ncrew has set up a course,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.26,0:37:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and i'm just supposed to drive\nas fast as i can in reverse.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.47,0:37:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,i'm actually pretty curious\nhow this is gonna turn out.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.73,0:37:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: this final farewell is\na half mile of twists and turns.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.54,0:37:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's got a whole lot\nmore besides...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.91,0:37:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,as the guys have put the movie\nmayhem back into this myth.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.48,0:37:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's not just the props.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.09,0:37:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,we're gonna put a little\npressure on adam,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.92,0:37:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,because i'm gonna be\nin a cop car
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.56,0:37:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,on his ass the whole way,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.59,0:37:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,with the sole exception that,\nwhen he sees me and takes off,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.23,0:37:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,i'm gonna be outside my car.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.63,0:38:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,so he's gonna have just\na little bit of a head start.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.47,0:38:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: adam's goal,\nlike the classic hollywood hero,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.40,0:38:08.51,Default,,0,0,0,,is to make it to the finish line\nbefore those pesky police.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.51,0:38:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,that is a cop.\nthat's bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.34,0:38:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: but with reverse gear\nhis only option,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.81,0:38:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,will he escape to victory?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.02,0:38:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,here we go. bye, cop.\n[ tires squeal ]
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.85,0:38:20.95,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: the chase is on.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.95,0:38:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,here we go.\ngettin' the heck outta here.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.92,0:38:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: and by the time\njamie's got going,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.19,0:38:27.49,Default,,0,0,0,,adam's already out of sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.49,0:38:29.29,Default,,0,0,0,,make a right-hand turn here.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.30,0:38:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,don't let go of that wheel.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.40,0:38:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: by shifting to\nthe central position,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.07,0:38:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,he's able to navigate\nwith skill.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.40,0:38:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,whoa. flaming car! dude.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.10,0:38:40.97,Default,,0,0,0,,oh, man.\npost-apocalypse.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.97,0:38:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator:\nat least, when he wants to.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.31,0:38:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,i want those boxes.\ncome on. yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.35,0:38:49.58,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: but while his steering\nis supreme...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.58,0:38:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,i don't know where he is.\ni hope he's not close.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.79,0:38:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: his speed, while fast,\nis no match for jamie.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.79,0:38:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,oh, fruit stand.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.92,0:38:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,i'm not gonna miss\nthe fruit stand.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.67,0:39:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,whoa! aah. oh! [ laughs ]
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.44,0:39:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: adam may be down,\nbut he's not out,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.98,0:39:18.54,Default,,0,0,0,,as he reverses back uphill...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.55,0:39:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,ah, i'm going still!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.68,0:39:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,narrator: a strategy that\nthe hyneman then copies.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.69,0:39:28.59,Default,,0,0,0,,with both drivers now revving\nin reverse,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.59,0:39:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a case of who's gonna\nblink first.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.19,0:39:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,[ tires squeal ]
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.36,0:39:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,oh! [ laughs ]
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.03,0:39:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.87,0:39:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,yet another in the long line of\nthings that we should just
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.37,0:39:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,set up for the public\nand charge money for.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.01,0:39:47.41,Default,,0,0,0,,that was awesome.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.41,0:39:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,step out of the car\nwith your hands up.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.84,0:39:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,okay. [ laughs ]
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.61,0:39:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that was so much fun.\n- [ laughs ]
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.98,0:40:00.45,Default,,0,0,0,,oh, my god.\nthat was the best thing ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.06,0:40:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,well, that went pretty much as\ngood as i could have imagined.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.73,0:40:08.49,Default,,0,0,0,,first off,\nthe course was amazing,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.50,0:40:11.33,Default,,0,0,0,,full of all sorts of\nreally interesting obstacles,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.33,0:40:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,from fruit stands to dudes\nfixing their cars to,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.67,0:40:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,come on, a flaming car.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.20,0:40:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,i also was able to go through it\nreally fast, i mean,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.51,0:40:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,fast enough where i almost lost\ncontrol of the car on a couple
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.28,0:40:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,of the straightaways.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.51,0:40:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,like, it started fishtailing.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.48,0:40:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,but because of brian's training,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.88,0:40:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,i was able to bring the car\nback under control.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.45,0:40:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,oh, oh, almost lost\na little control there.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.95,0:40:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,then, i actually spun out\nwhen jamie hit me.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.56,0:40:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,but again, in reverse,\ni bolted back up the hill.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.76,0:40:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and jamie chased me, and it was\nall going pretty good.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.70,0:40:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,but i was going too fast on\nthe accelerator and i spun out.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.20,0:40:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,he jammed into my front wheel,\nand i could not move.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.23,0:40:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,test over.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.31,0:40:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,so how do you wanna call it?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.64,0:40:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,i have to say,\ni started this story
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.38,0:40:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,thinking it was gonna be\nhandily busted.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.35,0:41:01.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and i am now thinking that\nit's actually plausible,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.65,0:41:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that it's not unreasonable\nhow much speed
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.52,0:41:06.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and maneuverability you can get\ngoing in reverse.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.45,0:41:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah, i mean, both of us,\ni think,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.99,0:41:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,if we had our choice would go,\nyou know, front forward, um,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.86,0:41:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,'cause that's gonna be\nyour better option.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.70,0:41:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's surprising\nhow good it can be.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.50,0:41:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,let's call it plausible.\nall right.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.53,0:41:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,i'm gonna drive forward home,\nthough.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.23,0:41:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,if you can.\n- [ laughs ]
